[ANALYSIS]
The experiment `bow_opt_20260514_112347_run_09` successfully executed a Bag of Words (BoW) model with a TF-IDF vectorizer, achieving an F1 score of 0.7233 and accuracy of 0.78. The configuration used a logistic regression classifier with a regularization parameter `C` set to 0.89775, limited the vocabulary size to 10,000 features, and applied a minimum document frequency threshold of 5. The model utilized unigrams only (`ngram_max=1`) and employed a validation split of 20%. 

While the model performed reasonably well with an F1 score above 0.7, there is room for improvement. One potential area to explore in future runs could be tuning the hyperparameters further, such as adjusting the regularization strength `C`, experimenting with different n-gram ranges, or trying other vectorization techniques like word embeddings. Additionally, increasing the vocabulary size might capture more nuanced patterns in the data, potentially boosting performance.